description.narrative: (Azerbaijan): .The Women's Participation Program (WPP) will continue.supporting activities that improve the status of women in Azerbaijan by.promoting women's entrepreneurship and small- and medium-size business.development, helping more women to take on leadership roles and engage in.decision-making processes, and strengthening the capacity of state.organizations to address women's issues. As the activity has evolved, more.emphasis is being placed on sustainability and ensuring that women.entrepreneurs and leaders are able to mentor and assist their peers. Increase.collaboration with the government is also a priority, and WPP activities will.include providing the ASAN Service (State Agency on Public Services and Social.Innovations under the President of the Republic of Azerbaijan) with a.professional development training program for female employees and volunteers,.conducting business leadership training programs, and organizing summer schools.on women's empowerment in vulnerable regions of Azerbaijan where women have.less access to employment and few community leadership opportunities..Supporting vulnerable women also increases economic opportunities and provides.strong leadership in areas susceptible to violent extremism...These activities contribute to the goal of sustainable economic.development (JSP 2.2 and ICS Goal 2.2)... .
